ates''' by average weekday paid [[newspaper circulation|circulation]] in 2019, including digital circulation.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cision.com/us/2019/01/top-ten-us-daily-newspapers/ |title=Top 10 U.S. Daily Newspapers |website=Cision |date=January 4, 2019 |access-date=2019-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190722203322/https://www.cision.com/us/2019/01/top-ten-us-daily-newspapers/ |archive-date=July 22, 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"border: gray solid 1px; border-collapse: collapse;\" cellpadding=\"5\"\n|- valign=\"top\"\n! Rank\n! Newspaper\n! Primary service<br>area\n! Headquarters\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | Total<br />circulation\n! Owner\n! class=\"unsortable\" |[[Nameplate (publishing)|Nameplate]]\n|-\n|1\n|''[[USA Today]]''\n|[[United States|National]]\n|[[McLean, Virginia]]\n|1,621,091\n|[[Gannett Company]]\n|[[File:USA Today (2020-01-29).svg|162px]]\n|-\n|2\n|''[[The Wall Street Journal]]''\n|[[United States|National]]\n|[[New York City]]\n| 1,011,200\n|[[News Corp (2013\u2013present)|News Corp]]\n|[[File:The Wall Street Journal.svg|160px]]\n|-\n|3\n|''{{sort|New York Times|[[The New York Times]]}}''\n|[[United States|National]]\n|[[New York City]]\n|483,701\n|[[The New York Times Company]]\n|[[File:NewYorkTimes.svg|160px]]\n|-\n|4\n|''[[New York Post]]''\n|[[New York metropolitan area]]\n|[[New York City]]\n|426,129\n|[[News Corp (2013\u2013present)|News Corp]]\n|[[File:New York Post.svg|160px]]\n|-\n|5\n|''[[Los Angeles Times]]''\n|[[Los Angeles metropolitan area]]\n|[[Los Angeles, California]]\n|417,936\n|[[Patrick Soon-Shiong#Investments|Nant Capital]]\n|[[File:Los Angeles Times logo.svg|160px]]\n|-\n|6\n|''[[The Washington Post]]''\n|[[United States|National]]\n|[[Washington, D.C.]]\n|254,379\n|[[Jeff Bezos#The Washington Post|Nash Holdings]]\n|[[File:The Logo of The Washington Post Newspaper.svg|160px]]\n|-\n|7\n|''[[Star Tribune]]''\n|[[Minneapolis-Saint Paul]]\n|[[Minneapolis, Mi